# SMS Spam/Scam Detection AI

This is a **text classification AI model** that can detect whether a message is **spam (scam)** or **ham (legitimate)**. It uses **Naive Bayes** and **TF-IDF vectorization** to classify SMS messages.

---

## ğŸ“Œ Features

- Detects spam and legitimate messages
- Works with any text message input
- Accuracy: ~96% on the SMS Spam Collection Dataset
- Simple, fast, and easy to use

---

## ğŸ—‚ Dataset

- **Source:** [SMS Spam Collection Dataset on Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/uciml/sms-spam-collection-dataset)
- **Size:** 5,572 messages
- **Columns:**
  - `label` â†’ `ham` (legitimate) or `spam` (scam)
  - `text` â†’ the message content

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Technologies Used

- Python 3.x
- Pandas
- scikit-learn (Naive Bayes, TF-IDF, train-test split)

---

## âš¡ How It Works

1. **Load dataset** â†’ CSV file from Kaggle  
2. **Preprocess data** â†’ Keep only relevant columns, clean labels  
3. **Vectorize messages** â†’ Convert text to numbers using TF-IDF  
4. **Train Naive Bayes model** â†’ Learn patterns between words and labels  
5. **Predict new messages** â†’ Detect spam or ham  

---

## ğŸ“Š Model Performance

- **Accuracy:** 96%  
- **Confusion Matrix:**  

| Actual \ Predicted | ham  | spam |
|------------------|------|------|
| ham               | 965  | 0    |
| spam              | 42   | 108  |

- **Precision, Recall, F1-Score:** Good balance, especially strong at detecting legitimate messages  

